(dp2
S'introduction_text'
p3
S"You awaken and everything is blurry. You sit up, rub your eyes and notice that you somehow have arrived in the middle of a beach. Your clothes are torn, and your throat is a little sore. Slowly you get up to your feet and look around. This is the start of long and wonderful journey. You must use logic, as well as wits and courage. You don't know how you got here, but maybe you can get home."
