Nsbssg21
S"You are standing at the top of the hand-carved staircase that leads up the side of a mountain. You have reached a wide open, flat, circular area which is covered with square stone tiles. Pilliars of various heights and widths are placed around the vicinity.\012\011At the center of a partiuclar square on the ground are four smaller stone tiles, shaped into quarter-circles, providing a stark geometric contrast to the square tiles. Behind four quarter-circle tiles stands another circular pillar, this one much thicker than the others that encircle this area.\012\012\011On top of each of the pillars that line the area are situated various three-dimensional geometric shapes that have been carved out of either glass or crystal, something which you can not be sure about due to their height above you. Regardless of the material, each work is an elaborate and beautiful piece, whose delicate curves catch and reflect the sun's light. Rainbows of varying hues are cast all about this area, but especially upon the center pillar.\012\012\011In the center of the large center pillar, a large sphereical container (made from a material similar to the geomtric shapes that line the other pillars) is half-filled with a clear liquid that glissens in the rays of light. Directly before you is a short and stubby cylindrical column with extremely elaborate marks and patterns etched onto its surface. Behind you to the south, the hand-carved staircase leads Down the mountain to the clifftops below."
sg22
S''
