S'The sand on this beach is very gritty, with many weeds growing in patches that thicken to the south. The ocean washes up gently along the shoreline; its waves having already been broken by a small peninsula that extends from the island east of here. The peninsula terminates into a wooden dock just north of you, across the water.'
sg22
S'You can go South to the north shore of the lagoon, or SouthEast into a dense patch of reeds.'
