S'You are standing in the middle of a thick patch of reeds and other knee-high plants. The soil is very wet and marshy in this area, a trend that continues off to the east, where the earth becomes very swamplike. You have absolutely no desire to trudge through a swamp in you current condition, so heading east would be out of the question.'
sg22
S'You can go West to the north shore of the lagoon, or NorthWest across the reeds, towards the ocean.'
