S"The cliffs part to the west here, allowing you access to a small river that has eroded its way through the stone over the ages. The river feeds from the ocean far ahead to the north, and weaves its way through the mountainside to the south, where it takes a turn westward. To the north the wind has gathered sand from the lagoon's shore into a small sand dune, and to the east of you an exotic coral reef stretches across the lagoon."
sg22
S'You can head West to where a group of rocks cross the river, North to the small sand dune, or South to where a long wooden bridge crosses the lagoon.'
