S"After you place your lips around the small end of the conch, you close your eyes and blow. You think that you can hear something and your eyelids snap open. Before you stands a huge winged unicorn. It doesn't look frightened, so you walk over, pet its long mane, and climb up onto its back. You are now riding on the back of a beautiful winged unicorn. It reminds you of the mythological creature 'Pegasus'. You can see most of the island from up here. Apparently the western part of the island drops off about 100 feet or so, and most of the plant life is on the lower and eastern half. You can see a lagoon on the northeastern part of the island, and a volcano on the southwestern portion. The unicorn is descending now. (Please return your seats to an upright position)"
sg22
