S"The western passageway up the volcano ends abruptly here, after turning south and overhanging a large alcove that has been cut into the rock below you. You can neither see nor hear anything that may be down there, and if you were to jump down there you probably wouldn't break any bones, but you most certainly would not be able to climb back up to this passageway."
sg22
S'You can either return East to where the three passways diverge, or you can chance jumping Down and finding out (for better or for worse) what lies within the aclove below you.'
