S'You are standing on the eastern end of a long wall that divides the western portion of the island, in the shade of a long branch that extends over the wall. From here you can see that the southwestern portion of the island is very rocky, the most prominant feature of which appears to be a small volcano. The northwestern portion of the island is far more flat and green, with a large grassy pasture stretching out to the horizon. Below you to the south is nothing but gnarled weeds and thorned foliage. To the north another wall splits off of the one you are standing on, forming a T shape.'
sg22
S'You can walk North to where another wall splits off, West along the current wall, or climb Up onto a branch that hangs over this end of the wall.'
