S'This is an oddly shaped plant, with white petals. You move your face to smell it\'s aroma, and it suddenly clamps around your nose and mouth. You cringe, prepared for some sort of violent act, but nothing of the sort occurs. Instead you realize with much excitement that it is providing you with a more than ample supply of oxygen! This wonderful specimen of foliage takes in your carbon dioxide and releases oxygen. You pull it back from your face and it easily detaches itself. You decide to call it an "oxoplant."'
