p24
sg9
I0
sg10
Nsg11
S'110-8'
sg12
S'This "obstruction" could have been implemented in the same manner as (for instance) the distance from the ledge over the river that runs through the mountains to the tree trunk on top of the mountain, but I felt that since the situation in which one needs a portable light source comes up so often, and is sovled by having a certain item as opposed to performing a different task, that implementing Darkness as an invisible obstacle my be better suited than setting up a series of Modifying ToWhichRoom Directional Objects. Implenting Darkness in this way was actually the orginal way in which all such problems where address, and I also wanted to show that there are many different ways to accomplish basically the same thing by mastering the Event Grammar of the COG Engine. By using this implementation, an ObstructedCompassGraphic will show that someone is capable of entering the darkness, but they currently cannot. If such a technique was used in the case of the tree stump example, the player would be given a hint that there must be *some* way to get up there.'
sg13
S"You can't see in the dark, you need light!"
sg14
Nsg6
